&lt;p&gt;Starting from the interview process and continuing into your career with us, you will be working by our four Operating Principles:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Performance: High standards, outstanding results,&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Impact: Big challenges, bigger results&l

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Overview&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;The Deployment Engineer will play an integral role in delivering our products to clients, collaborating closely with the commercial and engineering teams to ensure a seamless sales, integration, and deployment process. This position requires a highly organised and technically proficient individual with strong communication skills and a proactive approach to problem-solving.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The crux of the role will involve travel around North America to deploy our robots within warehouse sites. It is crucial you are able to travel for 1-2 weeks at a time.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Qualifications and Requirements&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comprehensive technical understanding of computer systems, with prior experience in autonomous hardware systems or computer vision applications preferred.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven hands-on experience with hardware in operational environments, including system assembly, disassembly, and on-site debugging.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as the primary customer contact for the deployment and installation of hardware and software platforms.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate with customers to plan and schedule installations, incorporating mechanical, electrical, software, and network components.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct on-site visits to execute system setup, configuration, calibration, and troubleshooting in accordance with project specifications.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop, maintain, and update installation, deployment, operational, and troubleshooting documentation for both customers and internal stakeholders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain effective communication with customers to resolve technical issues and ensure successful completion of deployment activities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What we need from you&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong software debugging and problem-solving skills, with demonstrated ability to address technical challenges effectively on customer premises.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent written and verbal communication skills, with the ability to present complex technical information clearly and professionally to diverse audiences.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Valid driving license required.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Benefits&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Starting from the interview process and continuing into your career with us, you will be working by our four Operating Principles:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Performance: High standards, outstanding results,&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Impact: Big challenges, bigger results&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Commitment: All in, every time&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;One team: One mission, shared success&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Joining our team and company isn&#39;t just about expertise; it&#39;s about embracing uncertainty with ambition. We&#39;re crafting world-changing solutions, fueled by a passion to redefine what&#39;s possible. We will look for you to help create and shape the future of logistics solutions through our products, our culture and our shared vision.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will also receive:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Health insurance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;401k&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;20 days annual leave&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Social security etc.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;AAP/EEO Statement &amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Dexory provides equal employment opportunities to all employees and applicants for employment. It prohibits discrimination and harassment of any type without regard to race, colour, religion, age, sex, national origin, disability status, genetics, protected veteran status, or any other characteristic protected by l

&lt;p&gt;The Deployment Technician works ahead of our Deployment Engineers to get warehouse sites ready for our robots. Travelling across North America, you will assemble and build robots on site, run initial tests to confirm they are fully operational, survey the warehouse environment, and verify that the power and connectivity requirements are in place,&amp;nbsp; setting the deployment team up for a smooth, predictable installation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a hands-on, travel-heavy role and the foundation of a clear career path: over time you will be trained on the full deployment process and grow into a Deployment Engineer, helping us build a strong, continuous pipeline within the team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role involves regular travel to warehouse sites around North America, typically arriving 2–3 weeks ahead of the Deployment Engineer’s installation visit. It is crucial that you are able to travel for extended periods, often 1–3 weeks at a time.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assemble and build robots on customer sites ahead of deployment, typically 2–3 weeks before the Deployment Engineer arrives to carry out the implementation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform initial testing and commissioning of each robot, confirming it is fully functional before handover to the deployment team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct detailed warehouse surveys and feed accurate site information back to the deployment team to inform installation planning.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Carry out detailed Wi-Fi and mobile/cellular connectivity surveys across the site, documenting coverage and flagging any gaps or risks.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Confirm with the customer that the required power supply and infrastructure are in place ahead of deployment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare, pack, and coordinate the return shipment of tools and equipment to our Nashville facility.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and maintain clear documentation of build steps, test results, site conditions, and survey findings for both customers and internal stakeholders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain effective communication with customers and the deployment team throughout the site-readiness phase.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Progressively build deployment expertise through structured on-the-job training, working towards a Deployment Engineer role.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications and Requirements&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hands-on experience assembling, building, or maintaining hardware or mechanical systems in operational environments, including assembly, disassembly, and on-site debugging.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comprehensive technical understanding of computer systems; prior experience with autonomous hardware systems or computer vision applications is preferred.&lt;/li&gt;
