&lt;li&gt;Help develop and improve testing procedures for both hardware and software systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Capture, analyse, and benchmark test data to measure robot performance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Use AI-powered tools and prompting techniques to extract insights and metrics from test results&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create clear and standardised testing processes for areas such as autonomy, data capture, and platform functionality&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with validating and approving software releases before deployment to production&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with cross-functional engineering teams to improve software release workflows and version control processes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support regular software release cycles and testing schedules&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help assess new features, verify bug fixes, and contribute to continuous product improvement&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What We’re Looking For&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A Bachelor’s degree in Engineering, Robotics, Computer Science, or a related field&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;An interest in software testing, hardware validation, or quality assurance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with robotics, autonomy systems, or data capture technologies is beneficial&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exposure to testing tools, automation, or scripting is a plus&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong problem-solving, communication, and teamwork skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A proactive attitude and eagerness to learn in a fast-paced technical environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
