&lt;p&gt;Starting from the interview process and continuing into your career with us, you will be

&lt;p&gt;At Dexory, we are building advanced, software-led robotics solutions that are redefining global logistics. Our multidisciplinary teams—spanning hardware, manufacturing, software, AI, and commercial—operate with pace, precision, and shared purpose. We are united by a collective ambition to deliver meaningful impact at scale.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We value ideas over hierarchy and execution over intent. We are builders, operators, and innovators committed to shaping the future of our industry.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a rare opportunity to join a company at a pivotal stage of growth and transformation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a commercially astute, strategically minded VP of People with a proven track record of scaling People functions in high-growth, complex environments. With over a decade of progressive People leadership experience, you will operate as a true enterprise-level People leader—equally comfortable setting global strategy and driving operational excellence.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will bring deep experience in building and evolving People functions from first principles, navigating ambiguity, and enabling international expansion across multiple jurisdictions. As a key member of the leadership team, you will play a critical role in shaping organisational capability, culture, and long-term business performance.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role requires a minimum of three days per week onsite at our Wallingford location.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are committed to building a diverse and inclusive organisation. We encourage applications from individuals who may not meet every listed requirement but bring the mindset, potential, and values aligned to our mission.&lt;/p&gt;
